# Korean Response Rule

- Always respond in Korean unless the user explicitly asks for another language.
- Explain implementation plans, errors, fixes, and summaries in Korean.
- Keep code identifiers, file names, package names, API names, and CLI commands in English.
- Do not translate technical keywords unnecessarily.
- When generating comments in source code, write comments in Korean only if comments are actually helpful.
